descp2: Geometrically, we consider the pixels of the input and output as squares rather than points. If set to `True`, the input and output tensors are aligned by the center points of their corner pixels, preserving the values at the corner pixels. If set to `False`, the input and output tensors are aligned by the corner points of their corner pixels, and the interpolation uses edge value padding for out-of-boundary values, making this operation independent of input size when `scale_factor` is kept the same. This only has an effect when `mode` is `'linear'`, `'bilinear'`, `'bicubic'` or `'trilinear'`. Default: `False`
